{"article_id":"7u7escE0fszhnH1C","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Are you affected by Tropical Storm Florence ?","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"When it 's safe ,","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"text , iMessage or WhatsApp your videos , photos and stories to CNN : 347-322-0415","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"( CNN )","depth":2},{"id":4,"text":"At least five people ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"including a mother and her infant ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"have died in North Carolina","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"as Tropical Storm Florence slowly moved from the Tar Heel State into South Carolina ,","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"officials said Friday .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"After coming ashore in North Carolina as a Category 1 hurricane ,","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"Florence was downgraded to a tropical storm Friday afternoon","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"and trudged into South Carolina","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"as night came .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Two people died in Wilmington","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"after a tree fell on their house ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"the city 's police department said .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"`` WPD can confirm the first two fatalities of Hurricane # Florence in Wilmington .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"A mother and infant were killed","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"when a tree fell on their house , ''","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"police tweeted Friday afternoon .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"`` The father was transported to","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"( New Hanover Regional Medical Center )","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"with injuries . ''","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Emergency responders pray in front of a home","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"after removing bodies","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"that had been trapped by a fallen tree .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"In the town of Hampstead , emergency responders","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"going to a call for cardiac arrest Friday morning","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"found their path blocked by downed trees .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"When they got to the home ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"the woman was deceased ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Chad McEwen , assistant county manager for Pender County , said .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"The fourth person","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"who died","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"was a man in Lenoir County","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"who was hooking up a generator ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"Gov . Roy Cooper 's office said .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Another man in the county","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"who was checking on his dogs outside","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"was killed in what his family thought","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"was a wind-related death Friday morning ,","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"emergency officials said .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Florence was inching along Friday night ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"trapping people in flooded homes","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"and promising days of destruction and human suffering .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Storm surges , punishing winds and rain are turning some towns into rushing rivers","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"-- and the storm is expected to crawl over parts of the Carolinas into the weekend ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"pounding some of the same areas over and over .","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"Billy Sample , a resident","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"stuck in the town of Carolina Beach , North Carolina ,","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"said Friday night :","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"`` The height of the storm did n't feel as bad","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"as it is now .","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"The house is shaking back and forth much more violently","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"than when the eyewall came through . ''","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"Sample said","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"when he looked outside of his house ,","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"which is about 1,000 yards from the beach ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"he saw the rain pooling up on the street","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"and what looked like storm surge coming up the road .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"In the besieged city of New Bern , rescuers had plucked more than 200 people from rising waters by midmorning Friday ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"but about 150 more had to wait","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"as conditions worsened","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"and a storm surge reached 10 feet ,","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"officials said .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"That number was down to 40 later in the day .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"- Florence 's location :","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"By 11 p.m. , Florence 's center was moving west-southwest through South Carolina at 5 mph , with maximum sustained winds of 65 mph .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"The center was about 20 miles north-northeast of Myrtle Beach .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Gradual weakening was expected Friday night ,","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"the hurricane center said .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"- Prolonged , dangerous winds :","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Tropical storm-force winds extend 175 miles","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Tropical storm-force winds extend 175 miles from Florence 's center .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"The storm is expected to lumber into far southeastern North Carolina and eastern South Carolina through Saturday ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"punishing the area with rain and damaging winds .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"- No electricity :","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"There were 788,916 homes and businesses without power Friday night ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"according to the North Carolina Emergency Management agency .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"- Flooding for miles :","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"Up to 40 inches of rain , and storm surges","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"pushing water inland","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"and not allowing rivers to drain ,","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"`` will produce catastrophic flash flooding and prolonged significant river flooding , '' the","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"Upto 40 inches of rain , and storm surges","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"pushing water inland","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"and not allowing rivers to drain ,","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"`` will produce catastrophic flash flooding and prolonged significant river flooding , ''","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"the National Hurricane Center says .","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"`` You 're going to have flooding miles and miles inland , ''","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"the center 's director , Ken Graham , said .","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"Some areas of South Carolina could see rainfall totals of up to 15 inches ,","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"forecasters said .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"- Record gusts :","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"Wilmington 's airport recorded a 105-mph wind gust","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"-- the fastest measured","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"since Hurricane Helene hit the city in 1958 ,","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"the National Hurricane Center said .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"Later Friday , a wind gust of 68 mph was measured at a station in Wrightsville Beach , near Wilmington .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"- Nuclear plant shutdown :","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"A nuclear power plant in Brunswick , North Carolina , shut down operations","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"because of the storm ,","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"the US Nuclear Regulatory Commission :","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"A nuclear power plant in Brunswick , North Carolina , shut down operations","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"because of the storm ,","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"the US Nuclear Regulatory Commission said on Twitter .","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"`` Plant procedures call for the reactors to be shut down before the anticipated onset of hurricane-force winds , ''","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"agency spokesman Joey Ledford told CNN .","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"Federal officials had said midweek","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"they were n't concerned about that facility or five other nuclear plants in the storm 's path ,","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"calling them `` hardened . ''","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"Expert scientists , however , had said","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"they were worried about Brunswick","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"because of scant public information about its readiness .","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"Rainfall totals for the storm will be similar to those in hurricanes Dennis and Floyd in 1999 ,","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"the National Weather Service 's Chris Wamsley said","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"`` The only difference is ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"back then it was within 14 days , ''","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"With Florence , `` we 're looking at the same amount of rainfall in three days . ''","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"One of the rescuers in New Bern was Jason Weinmann , a retired Marine","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"who has a military troop transport vehicle","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"he bought at a government auction .","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"He picked up 10 people on one run","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"and took them to a shelter .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"Jennifer Morales , 20 , said","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"there was 3 feet of water in her home .","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"`` It was pretty bad .","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"We did n't know where to go , ''","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"she said .","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"Another woman","depth":16},{"id":132,"text":"who was rescued by another group in New Bern","depth":16},{"id":133,"text":"told CNN 's `` Anderson Cooper 360 ̊ ''","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"that she and her family thought","depth":16},{"id":135,"text":"they would be safe in their brick home","depth":16},{"id":136,"text":"and heard","depth":16},{"id":137,"text":"the storm had been downgraded from a Category 4 .","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"`` About 11:30 , 12","depth":17},{"id":139,"text":"( midnight ) ,","depth":17},{"id":140,"text":"the water came into the house .","depth":16},{"id":141,"text":"It came in slowly","depth":17},{"id":142,"text":"but then it just steady , just kept rising , ''","depth":17},{"id":143,"text":"Annazette Riley-Cromartie said .","depth":16},{"id":144,"text":"She , her husband and three children went up into the attic for a while ,","depth":16},{"id":145,"text":"but the winds howled","depth":17},{"id":146,"text":"and the family descended to an upper floor bedroom .","depth":17},{"id":147,"text":"As they waited for emergency workers ,","depth":18},{"id":148,"text":"they heard neighbors calling for help .","depth":18},{"id":149,"text":"Her husband went","depth":20},{"id":150,"text":"to see","depth":21},{"id":151,"text":"if he could assist them","depth":21},{"id":152,"text":"but the water was chest high ,","depth":19},{"id":153,"text":"she said .","depth":18},{"id":154,"text":"`` It 's the worst feeling in the world","depth":18},{"id":155,"text":"to hear","depth":20},{"id":156,"text":"people yelling for help","depth":20},{"id":157,"text":"and you ca n't do anything , ''","depth":19},{"id":158,"text":"she said .","depth":17},{"id":159,"text":"An area in downtown Wilmington , North Carolina ,","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"usually meant for street parking and relaxing on park benches","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"is inundated by water from the swollen Cape Fear River .","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"Swift-water rescue teams from out of state helped local rescuers evacuate people","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"whenever conditions allowed .","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"One team from Maryland helped with about 40 rescues in New Bern","depth":14},{"id":165,"text":"starting Thursday ,","depth":14},{"id":166,"text":"member Mitchell Rusland said .","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"In Belhaven , the Pungo River roared into town ,","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"crashing up against homes at a waist-high level and higher late Thursday and early Friday ,","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"video from Amy Johnson showed .","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"Stay safe y'all !","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"pic.twitter.com/zYbKCKBLnY","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"- Michelle 🦄","depth":13},{"id":173,"text":"( @ chromatichues )","depth":13},{"id":174,"text":"September 14 , 2018","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"In Morehead City , Brooke Kittrell rode out the storm Thursday and Friday with her boyfriend aboard their docked boat ,","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"hoping","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"it did n't break loose","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"and slam something .","depth":14},{"id":179,"text":"She succeeded","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"-- staying awake all night ,","depth":14},{"id":181,"text":"retying broken dock lines in howling winds .","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"But there were times","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"she thought","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"they would n't survive ,","depth":15},{"id":185,"text":"she told CNN .","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"A boat is wedged in trees Friday in Oriental , North Carolina , in a photo from Angie Propst .","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"`` I honestly cried , ''","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"Kittrell said .","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"`` I was born and raised here","depth":15},{"id":190,"text":"and been through every storm the last 30 years ,","depth":15},{"id":191,"text":"but this one seems to be doing more damage","depth":15},{"id":192,"text":"than we expected . ''","depth":15},{"id":193,"text":"By Friday morning , the shore was flooded ,","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"and buildings were damaged , in video","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"she put up on Facebook .","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"In Jacksonville , North Carolina , city officials posted photos of toppled gas pumps and a downed trees early Friday ,","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"warning residents to take shelter","depth":12},{"id":198,"text":"and avoid roadways .","depth":12},{"id":199,"text":"Officials in several states have declared states of emergency ,","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"including in the Carolinas , Georgia , Virginia and Maryland ,","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"where coastal areas are still recovering from summer storms .","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"High winds and a storm surge from then-Hurricane Florence hit Swansboro , North Carolina , on Friday .","depth":10},{"id":203,"text":"Florence is one of four named storms in the Atlantic .","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"According to the National Hurricane Center ,","depth":10},{"id":205,"text":"the storm will travel through upstate South Carolina ,","depth":11},{"id":206,"text":"be downgraded to a tropical depression ,","depth":13},{"id":207,"text":"then turn north toward the Ohio Valley .","depth":13},{"id":208,"text":"As it moves near Ohio and West Virginia ,","depth":14},{"id":209,"text":"it will become a remnant low .","depth":14},{"id":210,"text":"Then it will swing to the northeast in the middle of next week on a path to the Atlantic Ocean near Nova Scotia ,","depth":14},{"id":211,"text":"where it will be an extratropical low with gale-force winds .","depth":14}],"relations":[{"parent":423,"left":214,"right":422,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":214,"left":0,"right":213,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":213,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":422,"left":3,"right":421,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":421,"left":222,"right":420,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":218,"right":221,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":217,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":217,"left":216,"right":7,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"